  "prompt": "How much does an average self publishing author make on Amazon?",
  "response": "The income of a self-publishing author on Amazon can vary significantly based on various factors including genre, marketing strategies, book quality, and audience reach. As of my latest data:\n\n1. **Successful Authors**: Some successful self-publishing authors can earn thousands of dollars per month. Top earners might make six-figure incomes annually.\n\n2. **Average Authors**: On average, many self-publishing authors might earn between $500 to $1,000 per month, although this can vary widely. Some might earn less, particularly newcomers or those with less effective marketing strategies.\n\n3. **New Authors**: New authors or those without established audiences might earn very little initially, sometimes only a few dollars per month until they build a reader base.\n\nIt's important to note that self-publishing requires effective marketing, continuous writing, and sometimes investment in quality production elements like editing, cover design, and advertising to boost earnings.\n\nFor more specific insights, authors often share their experiences and income reports on websites and forums dedicated to self-publishing.",
